title: Round 5: Extractor Quality — B→B+ & A-Grade Push
content:
# Round 5: Extractor Quality — B→B+ Promotions & A-Grade Push

## 11 Tasks

### Priority 1: B → B+ (4 tasks)
1. **C** — Struct/union fields as Field children
2. **C++** — Template variable extraction + typedef handler
3. **Ruby** — Struct.new detection + module_function + dead code
4. **R** — Fix identifier matching + remove synthetic IDs

### Priority 2: Cross-cutting quality (2 tasks)
5. **LazyLock regex** — Final sweep (Zig, Vue, SQL, Java — 7 sites)
6. **Code quality** — SymbolKind corrections (CSS, HTML), dead code (Regex, SQL), UTF-8 safety (Razor)

### Priority 3: B+ → A feature push (4 tasks)
7. **Rust → A** — Grouped/glob imports + macro fix + static→Constant
8. **Python → A** — Wildcard imports + class name fix + lambda naming
9. **TypeScript → A** — Decorators + access modifiers
10. **Kotlin → A** — Secondary constructors + double return type fix

### Priority 4: Documentation (1 task)
11. **Audit doc update** — Re-rate all extractors, evaluate B+ for A promotion

## Expected outcome
- Zero B-rated extractors (all → B+)
- 4 new A promotions (Rust, Python, TypeScript, Kotlin)
- ~10+ B+ extractors re-rated to A after review
